news.title: Land acquisition for Hyderabad metro rail phase-II in full swing: HAML
news.para: ​As per the directions of Telangana Chief Minister A Revanth Reddy, the acquisition of the identified 1,100 affected properties is progressing at a brisk pace, Hyderabad Airport Metro Ltd (HAML) Managing Director NVS Reddy said.

news.title: Malkangiri will get cement factory soon: Odisha CM
news.para: ​"A cement factory with an investment of Rs 4,000 crore will be set up in the district. This will provide employment for about 2,000 people in Malkangiri," the CM said.

news.title: Worldwide Realty to invest Rs 320 crore to construct 22-acre project in Manesar
news.para: "In this 22-acre project, we have already sold some housing plots. Now, we are launching 400 independent floors for sale," said Vikas Aggarwal, Chief Operating Officer of Worldwide Realty Pvt Ltd.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body resorts to public shaming of property tax defaulters
news.para: The decision was taken after many tax defaulters failed to pay up despite repeated notices. The corporation also issued notices, threatening to disconnect water and sewer connections, but to no avail.

news.title: NDMC plans two commercial complexes in Delhi
news.para: These commercial centres will be developed opposite Prithviraj Market and at a vacant plot adjoining Akbar Bhawan in Chanakyapuri.

news.title: Mumbai: Juhu residents allege authorities turning blind eye to construction pollution
news.para: They alleged that the sites have not been properly covered and work continues late into the night in one of the projects. The BMC failed to act against the developers despite several complaints.

news.title: Pune sees 11% drop in property registration during November 2024: Report
news.para: As many as 14,988 units were registered in November last year. Registration of properties fell 36 per cent in November compared to 20,894 units in October this year.

news.title: London approves plan for joint-tallest tower in Western Europe
news.para: The proposed 309.6-metre (1,015.75-foot) tall tower, which will be exactly the height of London's Shard south of the River Thames, was approved after a previously consented scheme was revised "to better respond to post-pandemic office needs", the City of London local authority said on Friday.

news.title: MoEFCC panel declines residential project proposal on private forest land in Thane
news.para: The state's nodal officer, despite strongly advocating a builder's pleas for a residential colony on 10.685 hectares of private forest land in Walshet, Thane district, faced rejection from the FAC.

news.title: Bhagalpur civic body launches drive to register 14,000 shops
news.para: The objective is to rationalise BMC's development plans across the 51 wards while boosting revenue. Currently, about 2,500 registered shops generate around 40 lakhs in revenue, but the BMC aims to register 14,000 businesses.

news.title: MADC to acquire 229 hectares for airport in Gadchiroli
news.para: MADC will be taking over 229 hectares land, which includes private and govt holdings for the project to be developed by it, says the GR. The land is spread over four villages — Murkhada, Pulkhal, Kanori, and Mudjha.

news.title: Lucknow development body to cancel 292 plots in Transport nagar scheme over missing records
news.para: The LDA has now asked the current occupants of these plots to submit allocation-related documents. These documents will be verified, and if found valid, the plot will remain with the current occupant.

news.title: Mangaluru civic body fixes fresh deadline for on-site composting in apartments
news.para: Accordingly, bulk waste generators, including large apartments, complexes, and business establishments in the city, will have to process the wet waste on-site using composting methods to produce fertiliser by Jan 15, 2025.

news.title: Bombay HC criticizes Maharashtra government over encroachments in SGNP
news.para: "We want the park to be restored at the earliest. We will not permit it to be damaged. Not at any cost," said a bench of Chief Justice Devendra Kumar Upadhyaya and Justice Amit Borkar.

news.title: Goa: ED seizes 19 properties in Anjuna and Assagao over land grab case
news.para: The ED provisionally attached the immovable properties under Sub-section (1) of Section 5 of the Prevention of Money-Laundering Act (15 of 2003) as ordered by the deputy director of the ED, Panaji zonal office, Goa.

news.title: Karnataka HC seeks government's response on PIL challenging e-khata mandate
news.para: A division bench comprising Chief Justice NV Anjaria and Justice KV Aravind gave this direction after hearing petitioner S Gowrishankar, a resident of Bengaluru.

news.title: Gujarat CM inaugurates Rs 550 crore Atal Smart City in Rajkot
news.para: The robust infrastructure, with all modern facilities, was created in TP scheme number 32 at a cost of Rs 550 crore.

news.title: Alkem Laboratories's promoter buys apartment for Rs 185 crore in Mumbai’s Worli
news.para: Seema Singh has bought this apartment spread over a total 14,000 sq ft on the 30th floor of the tower directly from the project developer Macrotech Developers.
